lenders.name: Bryan
lenders.loan_because:
I am religious, and I recognize that my religion encourages me to think freely*.  Pure religion is (to paraphrase) to help those in need; to love my neighbor.  Micro-finance seems to offer an avenue by which to extend assistance, while not depriving people of responsibility - a hand-up towards self-reliance.

My geographic focus is Honduras.  I was very impressed by the efforts of the people of this country to buck world opinion in 2009, and to demonstrate a willingness to uphold that country's constitution.  Honduras faces much head-wind already, but there is clearly an 'institutional' desire by its people, to do right by the voice of the body collective.

Also, I'm intrigued by this micro-finance concept.  I hope to learn more about the relationship b/n the cost of this capital vis-a-vis the experienced default rates, especially via this non-profit/non-traditional lending mechanism.

(*  I recognize that all of us on this earth, are children of a loving God.  With that recognition, I strive to love all of my brothers and sisters - irrespective of their beliefs and practices, in as much as they do not deny others of that same freedom to have moral agency - free to choose action, but also accountable for consequences.  In the oft used phrase, "Can't we all just get along?"   Cheers!)
lenders.occupational_info:
I earned an MBA from a top-tier, graduate school.  While my current profession is not lending, it does include a credit process (i.e. extensive financial-statement analysis ... not just a credit score).

While my current firm is relatively aggressive in extending a sort of unfunded financial participation, as a steward of that firm's capital I have a responsibility to honor the requests of the capital providers.  Kiva offers appeal, as it allows me to be the capital provider (albeit on a much small scale ... at least for now), and to therefore apply a less constrained approach - though the experienced default rates of the lending organizations coordinating some of these loans is very impressive.
